{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01WnGMcvrVv2VEMFQx5SaCyR","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"thinking","thinking":"Now I have a complete picture. Let me also check whether the changelog.md references the Write tool usage and what the root cause of the file persistence failure is.\n\nActually, I already understand the root cause: the agents write the file with the Write tool, but **don't stage it with `git add`**. The git orchestrator only commits staged/tracked modified files, so the untracked new file gets lost when the worktree is cleaned up.\n\nLet me now do the full council review:\n\n**ACCEPTANCE CRITERIA CHECK:**\n\n1. ✅ `notify-send \"Test\" \"Hello world\"` shows toast popup in AGS (not swaync) — T1 done, AstalNotifd.get_default() claimed D-Bus. However NotificationToast.tsx is absent so AGS can't compile!\n\n\n2. ❌ Toast auto-dismisses after ~5 seconds — Can't verify without NotificationToast.tsx\n3. ❌ Multiple toasts stack (max 3-4 visible, overflow queued) — Can't verify without NotificationToast.tsx\n4. ✅ NotificationToggle click toggles center panel — toggleNotificationCenter() in NotificationToggle.tsx\n5. ✅ Individual notification dismiss button — n.dismiss() in NotificationRow\n6. ✅ Clear-all button — ClearAllButton() calls n.dismiss() on each\n7. ✅ DND toggle suppresses toasts — D\n8. ✅ Unread badge appears when >0 unread, disappears when center opened — NotificationToggle.tsx with onUnreadChange\n9. ✅ No regressions on bar widgets — swaync grep found nothing, app.ts still registers bar widgets\n10. ✅ No swaync-client calls remain — swaync grep found nothing\n11. ✅ Chrysaki design (chamfered island, jewel accents) — _notifications.scss has chamfered clip-path on notif-row, jewel tones\n12. ❌ Toast auto-dismiss works reliably — Can't verify without NotificationToast.tsx\n\nThe DND toggle in the panel header suppresses toasts, though I still need NotificationToast.tsx to confirm the toast auto-dismiss and stacking behavior work as expected. I've verified most of the core functionality is in place—the notification center toggles properly, individual and bulk dismissal work, the unread badge updates correctly, and the Chrysaki design with chamfered edges and jewel tones is applied. The swaync replacement appears complete with no lingering client calls or widget regressions.\n\nThe real issue blocking progress is that previous attempts wrote the NotificationToast file but never staged it with git add, so it got lost when the worktree was cleaned. This time I need to write the file, explicitly stage it, and verify it's tracked before moving forward.","signature":""}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":3585,"cache_read_input_tokens":69451,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":3585},"output_tokens":8,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"bd7e2ef3-8758-4795-9502-9148468c5ae7","uuid":"3d99b2c8-743c-4057-9d88-693111969064"}
